A cousin of late President Umaru Yar’Adua, Arc. Ahmed Aminu Yar’Adua, and Sen. Shehu Sani have obtained their expression of interest and nominations forms to contest for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship tickets in Katsina and Kaduna states respectively in the 2023 elections. Addressing journalists after obtaining his forms, Yar’Adua said governance narrative in Katsina will change if he is given the opportunity to lead the state. The former National Inland Waterways Authority (NIWA) managing director, lamented the state of affairs in Katsina State, adding that the Aminu Masari-led administration has led the state into comatose. On his part, Senator Shehu Sani who represented Kaduna Central Senatorial District at the Eighth Senate said he wants to contest the election because he has the capacity to address the challenges facing the state, particularly, the problem of insecurity.